114.9	Solomon	Solomon	Solomon , according to the Book of Kings and the Book of Chronicles, a King of Israel and according to the Talmud one of the 48 prophets, is identified as the son of David, also called Jedidiah (Hebrew ) in 2 Samuel 12:25, and is described as the third king of the United Monarchy, and the final king before the northern Kingdom of Israel and the southern Kingdom of Judah split; following the split his patrilineal descendants ruled over Judah alone.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3d/Judgement_of_Solomon.jpg/220px-Judgement_of_Solomon.jpg
